My educational journey over the last 12 years has been nothing short of a mess. I went to CAU straight out of high school and got completely lost in the sauce. Made some insane life choices and ended up coming home the end of my junior year. Shortly after, I decided to enroll at FIDM and still was totally and completely lost and had no idea who I was or what I wanted. Did one semester and decided to quit…. Again. The world kicked my ass and I let it. For years. I started working and decided that was just what it was. Dropping out twice made me think school just wasn’t for me and I accepted my fate. Two years ago, shortly after giving birth to Jax, I knew that what I had accepted for myself simply was not enough so I silently decided to start over. I enrolled in classes as a freshman and started completely from scratch. My previous transcript was so terrible so I figured why not?! I didn’t tell anyone juuuuust in case things didn’t work out again. Lol. 

Yesterday, I completed my program and graduated with a degree in business (with honors!!!!!) and surprised everyone! What a wonderful feeling to know that I didn’t let the world stop me this time. I didn’t let myself or my fears get in the way. I did it for me and I did it for Jaxon and I’m going to keep doing it and keep going and evolving and growing and winning! I haven’t worn a cap and gown since 2011 and it was real cute okurrrrrrr. 🎓🤍

Just want to stop and thank God for all of the great things that are happening right now. I am 100% in a season of blooming and I feel so blessed and grateful. My prayer life is strong. My son is happy and healthy and smart and kind. I am in love with the sweetest man I have ever met and he treats me like a princess. My family is healthy. I received my associates degree in business with honors. I was just accepted into Pepperdine Business School and was awarded a merit scholarship because I AM THAT GIRL!!!!! My friendships are continuing to blossom and grow. My job is going fantastic. And quite frankly….. I look and feel the best that I ever have!!!!!!! ITS ME SEASON. 🪩✨

If I could, I would go back and tell this sweet little girl that she is allowed to be her own person. I would tell her that her dreams of being a spice girl were attainable. I would tell her that even though that sometimes she felt alone, she is extremely loved. As I reflect on my 20s, I feel very blessed to get off that ride lol. The last 10 years have been nothing short of a whirlwind but, God truly had his hand on me. I’ve been in a lot of places that I probably shouldn’t have come out of but with God’s grace (and a praying mama) I made it through every single time. I’ve learned so much. In 30, I will move in love, kindness and positivity. I will be open to love and joy and happiness. I will allow myself to receive and bask in all of the greatness and joy that crosses my path. I will keep dreaming, I will keep believing in myself, I will keep going. Baby cheech, I am going to keep making you so proud! You would think I was so cool 🥹🥹🥹🥹
